reviews.text: Went to visit on 06NOV22 around 3pm and was indirectly refused service. I walked in and greeted an older man near the back who immediately looked down, turned around and walked away from my line of sight pretending not to hear me. I frequent this location about once a week and I tip. Took my business elsewhere and intend to file a complaint with corporate.

The workers were extremely terrible and harassed me and my boyfriend because we were trying to get a smaller sized drink and no longer wanted the large. They tried to charge us extra even after switching the cups out and proceeded to yell and cuss at us.

I did not go to this Subway location 28Feb2020. I went to Keith and Sons Soul Food next door to the Subway. Please update your records.

My rating is not against Subway, it is against Google's inability to provide me with an accurate choice of reviews for the locations that are next door to each other.

The server was disrespectful. I walked in and forgot to replace my mask. He was yelling. I put it on apologizing for not putting it on. He continued to tell at me. His co-worker told him to calm down and he continued to tell. I left with my friend. Sale was half of what they could have made.
Great food. They always make our sandwich right! Great service

All I can say is delicious! I ordered a strawberry shortcake and my family was very satisfied. It was very tasty. The cake was very moist and it still tastes fresh after 3 days. I found a new bakery. Thanks again Sweet Tooth Bakery!

I ordered my son's birthday cake from here. I needed the cake a little over a week later and they got it done! Super cute cake! I have no complaints. My daughter also LOVES their strawberry cupcakes.

Thank you Sweet Tooth!

Very friendly staff and delicious food at an amazing price. I hadn't had a bean pie in decades and decided to get a few. One bite brought tears to my eyes. It was so amazing. I'll be back soon for some other things as well. Amazing place.

Let’s start it by saying the Rosette cake was huge! 5 Layers!!!! On top of that it was very beautiful we did not want to cut it lol. The lemon icing was perfect, tart but yet sweet. The cake was moist. My grandma loved it. 😍

The only concern I have,  is to improve in designing cake to meet custom cake visions of the customers. They are still good that would be the cherry on the cake, if your team master design.

The customer service is out of the roof, very professional.

The taste of the cake is fresh, moist, not to sweet and nice flavors.
I would definitely recommend and buy again.

Thank you for such a delicious cake that my guests are raving about.

Have been going here for just about 10 years, food has always been delicious. They have the best buffalo wings I've ever had and are very addictive. For the most part negative reviews are from negative people. The restaurant is family owned and are the kindest people.
The food was really good. The customer service was great and we will definitely be going back.

Customer service is trash 🗑️ . Receptionist is rude and disrespectful.  The food is disgusting and when they don't answer the line states they have COVID and are going to be closed for two weeks worst  carry out ever.

I ordered shrimp and wings and they forgot my cocktail sauce and buffalo sauce and. Then asked me if I can just get it next time I order, because it would take the driver too long to come back out!! Will not be ordering from there again.  (Update)Just tasted my food …🤬 fries dry as hell and my spicy shrimp it’s spicy!! Smh
Food was not good. The shrimp egg roll tastes like it had cinnamon nasty. It took 30 minutes. They charged me more than their menu said don't go there

plus_code.compound_code: V4QH+R9 Landover, Greater Landover, MD, USA

reviews.text:
So today about a few minutes ago my husband gave me this meal from Keith & Sons. I was so excited because I was craving some yams potato salad and meatloaf. Unfortunately to my surprise I opened my food and notice that my potato salad is in the same container with hot foods A big no for me. But I still wanted to give it a chance. I  then noticed that the yams are straight out of the can. Although I was not to upset about the canned yams. I then decided to go for the meatloaf and as you can see from the picture I got a big surprise with raw meat in the middle.  This right here is a Hard No for me.

I am just turned off at this point and the whole meal went in the trash. Unfortunately to say I will not be buying anything from this place again.

Oh and no I don’t give it any stars. I just had to do so in order to post

Went to Keith and sons for the 1st time today. I had the French toast, cheese eggs, bacon and a side of grits. The food was pretty tasty and a good portion side. The service was also pretty quick compared to other reviews I've read. I'll have to come back for dinner and see if I like it.
Just something about this place that keep us coming back. The best breakfast and Soul food spot in Town...

Food was Mid Grade. Waited in line for over 30 mins. They only had one Person and the cook working . So the line moved every 10 minutes.
I got the Baked Mac and cheese , with Fried chicken (oxtail Gravy)
And a piece of baked chicken .
The Mac n cheese had no flavor , very bland, the chicken was not cooked all the way through I could barely rip the pieces in half . Very big wings so they surly need to be cooked longer . I give the food a 5 the backed chicken was decent that’s why it got a 5. I truly want a refund but I just won’t waste money here again.

The Chicken wasn't cooked all the way
Macaroni, Cheese was bland. Didn't taste it. The flavor of the cheeses

The Greens were salty.

Other than that, it was a good portion
I will attempt to purchase another dinner

The workers were phenomenon very helpful

I ran a business once before
I monitor certain items in an establishment

The restaurant portion is clean. The service is spot on. There are very few disturbances. You definitely get what you ask for and it's delivered hot. What more can you ask for? They rely on the kiosk because it helps with time waiting. This is actually one of the better fast food places I've seen
The person helped us was pleasant. The sandwich was juicy and tasty but keeps falling apart halfway through. I had the spicy deluxe chicken & fish sandwich.

Tasty and clean, but Slowest "fast food" chain I've experienced. Every time I go to the drive through I have to go and park and wait because they are so slow.  My most recent experience there was almost no one else at the restaurant and I still was told to go in park and had to wait for my food.

They are so busy that the walk-in experience is pretty bad. First the self checkout machine is printing blank paper so you don't have a number, or a receipt if you keep those. Then you wait for a while, it's fast food but it's not so fast for walk-ins and everyone in the drive through gets the priority. Lastly, if you have any concerns you can stand there all day and they won't acknowledge and will be sure to avoid eye contact. My large fries 🍟 didn't look full (none spilled into the bag) but there was no one to talk to despite 2-3 employees within 5 feet of you. They were legit busy, but so am I that's why I came in for a fast food bite.

My friend gets the mcflurry all the time with extra oreo and add Carmel it's different at every store .. they don't stir it so all topping are on top and you don't tne toppings with every bite.. this store was ok but needs work on mcflurry.

This is ridiculous! I’ve been a customer for sooo long and I never received donuts like this. This batch was so thin and hard!!!! Krispy Kreme on Central Ave needs to do better! Every time I come they NEVER have regular glazed. Always run out but to charge me for these ugly looking donuts is beyond me. I’m very disappointed and I have to drive 25-30mins to this store because my grandfather doesn’t eat any other kind of donuts. They seal the box so tight I didn’t even noticed until I drove off smh…

I went here because I saw 3 cars in the drive-thru & figured it was safe even though I didn't see any Krispy Kreme signs in the window. The store looks really bad, super dark inside, & the drive-thru menu had signs missing.  The roof of the drive-thru is falling apart. I started to pull off because of the puddle of water inside, but guy walked up before I could. I asked him what the water was for, & he said the floor was being cleaned. There was a rack of donuts beside the puddle. The donuts looked a little odd, one was small, one smelled sour & one was not cooked enough. I threw them all away. I will say that the young man who took my order was very polite. I wish all the staff the best, but they, & the customers, deserve better.

This store is horrible. Every time i come here it’s an issue. They are very rude. I arrived at 7:40am. The door is still locked to go inside. This happened multiple times. They’re supposed to open at 6am. When I do finally get inside the guy tells me he can help me better if I go in the drive thru!!!
They only have 5 -6 options and it’s always the same basic ones and never any seasonal as they advertise. When I ask if course there is an attitude by the employees. They have also shrunk their doughnuts by a significant amount and increase the price close to $17 for a dozen.  That’s laughable honestly. There is plenty more pics but they just look horrible. Do better!

Horrible experience here! I ordered a Halloween dozen on Halloween day and they did not have them! They gave me dry doughnuts to make up for it and I also ordered a pumpkin spice latte and their machine was not working. I settled for a regular coffee but they didn’t have cream or sugar. Staff seems lost and place looks dirty and unkept. Would never go here ever again.

This Krispy Kreme location met my expectations with no disappointments. Only had to wait in the drive thru for a couple of minutes and the donuts tasted fresh and moist when I arrived home! I would definitely come back to this location!

name: Sardi's Pollo A La Brasa - Capitol Heights
vicinity: 8811 Hampton Mall Drive North, Capitol Heights

reviews.text: Chicken was tender and juicy. The sauce it came with is so creamy and has a touch of spiciness make the chicken taste so much better. Fried rice and fried yuca is ok. Empanadas was tasty as well. Overall affordable dinner meal for 2 people.

This was my first time going here and I like it. The three thousand 4.4 🌟 ratings in Google Maps made me curious if they were that good.  The chicken was juicy 😋 not charred or burnt and you had a choice of multiple sides not just French fries and yuca
I have been ordering the Greek Salad from Sardi’s as a meal form many years and it is always good. Today is was still good, however to salad is much smaller and cost more. It is now a side salad.

I got the pork and cheese pupusas, chicken and beef empanadas, and steak quesadilla. Pretty good overall. I wish I would have gotten more salsa for the quesadilla and a lime.The chicken empanada was bland and dry. That was disappointing given that the regular chicken is so juicy and flavorful. The steak empanadas were the opposite. Moist and tender shredded beef. Theyvforgot the dipping sauce so i cant aay if that would have made it better or not. Everything was hot! I even when I got home. Love that they made it to order. May just go back for more today! All total I spent $31 for 2 pupusas, 1 quesadillia (steak was extra), and 3 empanadas.

Food is good for carryout, but my favorite was the salmon skewers and roasted potatoes and they have disappeared from their menu. Check your bags too before leaving. For some reason, I am always missing a side that goes with a meal. Last time...fries that went with my salmon.

The Rainbow Trout tremendous super good fish , phenomenal flavoring and seasoning
Crab cake sandwich was tremendous satisfying as well as flavorful with a nice herbs, crunchy frys and great coleslaw!!

As I entered the place the first thing that struck me was how clean it was, I mean G I clean emaciate. What threw me off after that was the supposed store manager in a Cameroon seafood shirt very loud and obnoxious. I actually witnessed him untaped a box for no reason and tape it back up I don't know what he was doing but it looked like not standard procedure. Then when he engaged me as we were talking he was eating and food was falling outta his mouth ( check the camera 10/06/22 some time between 3:30 and 6:45) I was the gentleman with the cane. The lady who took my order and the cook in the back of the house were awesome and she got my order correct. Now there was another incident with the gentleman,(the supposed manager) a woman walked in she was about 6feet beautiful African American Queen after she gave her order and she left, he made more then one unsuitable comments about her and the staff laughed. I will never spend another dollar in there for that fact because black dollars matter and every customer should be treated with some type of respect. The woman will never know but I do and it's an unforgivable thing to have  manager or whom ever he is to do that even if she never heard anything I did and quite possibly my family members or I could be next. NO I'LL SPEND MY DOLLARS ELSEWHERE AND ANYONE OF COLOR SHOULD TO. BESIDES THE FOOD I RECEIVED WAS BLAND WITH NO TASTE.

The worst place to order seafood, especially DONOT order online! I ordered 1 dozen of crab and soup, they are all arrived frozen! If these are not freshly made, why we spend hundreds$ on this？！ Stay away from this place!

🚫🚫DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY!!This use to be a decent establishment, now it's just a trash facility! Ordered an ultimate and seafood platter and food was disgusting, unflavorful, tough and dry. Clearly the food was refried or reheated. The so called crabcake was stuck under the fish since it looked like a black bean veggie pattie and  was as hard as a hockey puck! Don't waste your money!!
The large male crabs 🦀 were 80.00 a dozen but it was worth it!!!!!! They tasted so good too.

Terrible. Can't even get soda right. The drink on the left isn't an iced tea, it's supposed to be a coke. They didn't use barely any syrup, it's all seltzer. This has happened multiple times. Not going to visit this location anymore.
Service is Terrible! New restaurant is nice though.
Drive up order was wrong, didn't discover until I was back home.  Otherwise it was fine.

Horrible I ended up getting a refund because the lady at the pick up window wasn’t ready to hand me my order so I looked away she was asking the manager if this was my order and he wasn’t responding to her so I turned my head and patiently waited for her to figure it out she calls out ma’am to get my attention I said I’m sorry and thank you as she hands me my drink. No your welcome she walks away to grab my food and as she’s doing that she says these people need to pay attention mind you the window was wide open so I heard her. I let it slide and then she gave me my food I asked for extra sauce her response is it ain’t in the bag just like that. I then ask to speak to the manager at this point he doesn’t even hear me out he shuts the window on me while I’m talking. I ask for corporate number he tells me he doesn’t have it. I will not be returning to this location

Manager for Thursday night January 13 at 1015 pm my husband was refused service and told to move out the way for next customer and then she wouldn’t even give her name or fix the situation I’ll make sure this McDonald is contacted by cooperative I should call my lawyer right now to see if we can have a pop to see how clean it is see how customer service is compared to the rest of the McDonald’s it’s really sad someone could be homeless and was given 10$ and all they wanna do is walk through the drive through area to get something to eat 😢  this lady just blocked her blessing

It’s bad enough drive-through is the only thing open. I ordered a combo paid for and was handed a small drink. I asked could I pay extra and get a large drink? I was told no they’ve already closed the register. I stated I didn’t know the drink came that small. she says yes it would’ve only been $.20 more. I had to ask several times can I pay the difference. I don’t mind paying finally she swapped it out. Bad customer service. Unfortunately, some employees make it bad on the rest.

Rude and food was old and nasty.  Wish it could bee zero stars. It is a fail every time I come to this one.  Don't know why I go back besides it's close to me. The pics are from a T2 XXXL GRILLED stuffed burrito beef. As you can see it's a rice stuffed burrito.
Food was very hot and very good great job 👏

Who's on Rest Room duties???
Love that Pot 🥧 Pie

Tried the chicken pot pie & REALLY enjoyed it. Good news, they're reasonably priced, made frm SCRATCH, DAILY, w/ F.R.E.S.H. ingredients &have a great, crispy crust.

Bad news, location2location, pot pies vary & the potpie I got here had 2much liquid, instead of being creamy. Also, they only cook a limited amount. So, don't expect 2 get1 late evening. Don't know the nutritional value. But, as good & filling as they R, can't b2 healthy every day🥺

This was my 1st time at this location.
Everyone was respectful, professional and personable.
Being a manager in retail myself, I can spot those on their phones and there was one, hiding between a machine and a wall. In her defense, my food wasn't ready but I'm sure there was something she could have been doing, as there is always something that needs to be done. 😊
Regardless, I will be returning.

Thank you for feeding us that are too lazy to cook. 🤣

This used to be my favorite Wendy's in the area but customer service has gone way down at this location. The whole experience was unsatisfactory. Showing kindness just didnt work. I always say thank you to the staff, no one says thank you back.

Thankfully the food was hot, however, my burger was dry.

Finally, I will not be visiting this location again for dining-in or drive-through.

Not every customer is a jerk, we do appreciate the service workers in all capacities. Please be kind.

Whoever is training, use the Chik-fila model, or even the McDonald's model across the street from you (we cant wait until they reopen, hopefully with same management)

This used to be my favorite Wendy’s. It’s turn into a rude unprofessional and unpleasant place. The African American dark melanin skin female with the braids in the drive thru was very short rude cutting me off as I was speaking in drive thru. I can understand if the long was long it wasn’t busy at all. She gave a fake smile. The cashier that got my payment was smiling and smirking I’m pretty sure he heard his unprofessional co worker taking my order. It’s sad we have unprofessionals like this in the black community. If you don’t like your job go find another one.
It's a Wendy's... the food isn't always as hot as i would like, but it's good. Services can be slow and usually are. The staff is decent but typically nonchalant.
Lady behind desk yelling, we waited in line are watched her just walk around not doing anything. Needs to train employees how to have better customer service skills

I stopped by Bull Wings for old times sake. It used to be my go to spot for breakfast, sometimes lunch, when I worked in the field. It's popular, convenient and reasonably priced. It's clean but doesn't really look like it because because it's old and faded. The food is still good. The menu is not very varied, but you can get a good basic meal that's tasty. It's a good alternative to the franchises because they offer scrapple, bologna and Italian sausage as options. The service isn't great and parking is sometimes a challenge but, overall, it's a good value for the money.
Simply the Best omelets around. You can't go wrong! My favorites are the Ham or Italian Sausage Omelet with green peppers,fried onion,and cheese 😋
Best place to eat breakfast 🍳 I’ve been coming to this spot for over 20 years and my breakfast is on point every time 😊 👍🏽

They have great breakfast and are pretty quick with their service. If you don't call your order in first it's usually only a 15 to 20 minute wait, depending on your order. I usually order for the family when I go. Never had a bad experience, you get what you ask for so be specific. They serve breakfast and lunch. They close at 12pm, they are closed on Sundays and the parking is trash because of their location. That can't be helped though. Still very much worth it!!!
Hot, fresh, cheap food

I wish I could get my money back. I spent well over an hour browsing through Uber Eats, deciding what to order and settled on Hot Pot Grill. Major mistake! The shrimp salad was nothing more than welted shredded lettuce that’s used for subs with a few carrots and cherry tomatoes tossed in. Furthermore, the shrimp was miniature. I also paid for extra pineapple jerk sauce and didn’t receive it. It’s a one and done for me.

The jerk chicken is pretty good tasting… spicy and definitely not a barbecue style like some places get away with. There were barely any beans in my rice and peas. Make sure to ask for white meat if that is your preference. The steamed vegetables were great.

Went for the first time a few weeks ago. Ordered oxtail for myself and partner to share. When we start eating we realize it’s a little bland for what we are used to for Jamaican cuisine but still good. However as we bite in further along we realize the “oxtail” I paid for was actually chicken. The meat was white . No clue if it was a genuine mistake but a little disappointing considering the price.
Customer service is nice! The beef patty was tasty and flaky! Oxtails were cooked tender and meat slid off the bone but the yellow rice, I’ll pass and oxtails need more seasoning, just too bland!
The Caribbean spices fill the air as soon as the door opens, so you know dishes are well seasoned. Great customer service from the cashier to the owner. Will be back to sample other dishes.

Very welcoming environment with a nice and professional staff.

I tried this place after receiving the brochure in the mail so I didn't know what to get. I ended up trying what was recommended which was E1, Collagen Beauty. I was pretty good and refreshing,  yet a little tart with collagen jelly which i thought was ice.

I also tried a tuna sandwich. I'll be honest... it wasn't what I was use to because it was made with yogurt, but they were very accomodating.

Very relaxing environment.  Beautiful establishment (inside & outside). I am coming on my cycle, and am looking for pain relief. I pray what she has offered,  helps. The lady here seems very knowledgeable, and she told me that she is a Nutritionalist. The menu looks great, nutritious and delicious and I look forward to incorporating her into my daily commute, for lunch, or a quick snack. We need more healthy options in our community. Let's keep her here 😉
Absolutely delicious and sugar free. The meal plans are amazing. The ladies are friendly and professional.

I wanted to give this place a shot, because it doesn't hurt to try something healthy. I decided to try a small lychee strawberry smoothie, suggested by the owner herself, and it did not disappoint. For something that is sugar free this was sweeter than I expected, which I enjoy. If this was a summer day, this would hit the spot, but on a 38° day it's still good. I would like to try other items here.
Very good,very fresh,natural and low calories.
I love their crabs they have a lot of meat in them even the smaller ones are heavy the best part is that they cook to order everything the picture was from Mother’s Day.

I always pick up about $85.00 or more worth of Large Shrimp and Crab Legs. I like to cook my own, so I come in, order and go!  The staff are always friendly, and the product is always fresh and substantial in size.  Good customer service is super important to me.  Once I  was introduced to Edwards, its my Go To place for seafood.  Look for the customer with the White Cooler coming in, that's me!

This place is hit or miss… Some days it’s the bomb & some days not so much. If you enjoy female crabs; they never run out. Customer service has improved over the yrs but still needs improvement. Can be quite rude to paying customers.
This is thee only place I buy my crabs from! Not only are the nice but the crabs and oysters are so good! If you want good seafood please check then out. I promise you won't be disappointed!
Crabs legs huge but very little meat inside. Shrimp are great.

name: Panda Express
vicinity: 8800 N, 8800 Hampton Mall Drive North, Capitol Heights

reviews.text: The most nastiest food I’ve had in my life. I asked for beef and broccoli they literally gave me three pieces of beef with a bunch of broccoli. Even dog food taste better than this

I like this Panda Express.  They give you real portions, the server smiles, the food is fresh, however.  I have a problem with the cashier lifting up my box to see the contents inside, after she's been collecting money.  Cashiers should not touch your containers after touching dirty but money with no gloves or with gloves unless you gonna change each time b4 you touch the food containers for that you get a 3 star. Health and safety first always and forever with me.  Bottom line.
30 minutes before closing, you eye challenging leftovers and slim...pickins...so how early. Lemonade used to be sooo good...watered down last few times
Lil stingy with the rice and lo mein especially for a bigger plate but food was fresh so it's all good

Kudos to the staff.
Very good customer service .
Trained well.
Food was excellent.
In one word - Scrumptious! The Jollof Rice is one of a kind. The fisherman soup will leave you speechless...No regrets at all.

Ordered through UberEats and I was not disappointed! The food is amazing and large portions for the prices! And the presentation is so pretty even for delivery. If your ordering through delivery I've Added pics so you can see what it looks like. I ordered the Grits with a crab cake and Beef sausage, Seafood macaroni, peach tea and the apple caramel egg rolls. I was not disappointed and I will order again!

Food was torch 🔥 everything was delicious.  We had the honey jerk wings, fried whiting, fried curry cabbage, smoked mac & cheese, zucchini & squash medley, spinach & crab dip. I will order online prior to going the next time; it takes some time to get your food; hey you can’t rush greatness. I will definitely go back to taste more things.

OMG!! The best Jerk chicken tacos I’ve ever eaten in my life! The honey lemon pepper (yes I said honey lemon pepper) were bomb! The Mac and cheese were bomb and the yams were on point!  Definitely will be going back again!

We went and ordered off of ChefRom menu. It's his birthday today, happy birthday. He wasn't their but the staff were extremely friendly and even brought our food to our car. Also, the food is delicious, lamb chops and beef egg rolls. We will try Lula Mae's Gardin food next time

Every now and then I come up on a spot that’s a gem…a diamond in the rough…a spot that’s exceptional. Well on this day…THAT HAPPENED!! This Soul filled Soulfood food truck has delectable vittles that made my day, you hear me!! With a update on traditional dishes, you’ll find some teriyaki seasoning, jerk seasoning, even some Tex-Mex is up in there. Go…thank me later!! To the lady that hipped me…THANK YOU!!
.

Items Reviewed:
Their Crab Soul Rolls (3 fried Eggrolls with seasoned crabmeat $15.99). STAMP!! Crispy, thick, well seasoned, & plentiful!!

Their Jerk Chicken Tacos (with cilantro lime slaw, cheese, lettuce, & tomato $10). STAMP!! Flavorful jerk chicken, on a fried flour tortilla!!

Their Crab & Spinach Dip-$9.99, & Grilled Cheese-$15.99 (seasoned crab meat, cheese, & spinach). STAMP them both!! Rich, meaty, with a hint of creamy Old Bay!!

They’re Loaded Grits (with Salmon, Shrimp, veggies, cheese, & a creamy seafood aioli $25.99). STAMP!! This thing was HUGE, creamy, & full of protein. Everything blended…WORKED!!

Their Maple Cornbread-$2.50…DELICIOUS!! Tasty, but a tad bit dry.
Their Strawberry Banana Pudding $6.99…STAMP!! There was a cake in this that had cinnamon in it!! A hint of strawberry, & a dollop of banana!! GREAT!!

Their Cucumber Mint Mango Lemonade…($5). STAMP!! Refreshing, palate cleansing, tasty!!
.

.

The Soul Rolls, Loaded Grits, Mango Lemonade, The Pudding, Grilled Cheese, & Tacos!!

I’ve been eating at The Chicken Man since they’ve first opened in Temple Hills and it has became one of my favorite soul food spots in PG. I’ve had the fried chicken wings w/ fries, the fish sandwich, the chicken quesadilla and my friend loves the salmon, chicken and shrimp bowl. I’m sure I had more but each meal comes with a corn muffin that is so bomb!

Recommended by one of the employees "Ralph" to give them a try. He discussed the menu, letting me know there's delicious food to satisfy everyone's palate! I am primarily vegetarian & occasionally pescitarian. The night I dropped in, I was able to meet "The Chicken Man" Everyone was so warm, friendly and welcoming. I ordered the shrimp box with fries, side order of greens and homemade ice tea. This food was delicious, the best I have had in a long time! Hot, tasty and well seasoned. I love this place, highly recommend. You definitely will be seeing me again soon😋♥️. Now the hater's giving a bad rating for Doordash and UberEATS is absurd!
